Organize output

# Extract parameters from fit object
par_ests = data.frame(extract(fit, c("gamma", "delta", "beta")))  %>%
  gather(key, value) %>%
  separate(key, c('par', 'subj'), sep='\\.')

# Add correct subject identifiers
par_ests = data.frame(subnum = unique(clean_beh_data$subnum)) %>%
  mutate(subj = as.character(1:n())) %>%
  right_join(par_ests, by='subj') %>%
  select(-subj)
par_ests %>%
  filter(par == "gamma") %>%
  ggplot(aes(value))+
  geom_histogram(alpha=.5, bins=50)+
  facet_wrap(~subnum, scales='free_y')+
  labs(title = "Posterior distribution of probability distortion",
       xlab="", ylab="")

par_ests %>%
  filter(par == "delta") %>%
  ggplot(aes(value))+
  geom_histogram(alpha=.5, bins=50)+
  facet_wrap(~subnum, scales='free_y')+
  labs(title = "Posterior distribution of lottery bias",
       xlab="", ylab="")

par_ests %>%
  filter(par == "beta") %>%
  ggplot(aes(value))+
  geom_histogram(alpha=.5, bins=50)+
  facet_wrap(~subnum, scales='free_y')+
  labs(title = "Posterior distribution of inverse temperature",
       xlab="", ylab="")
